.SH "Function Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "\fBsexp_t\fP * bfs_find_sexp (const char * name, \fBsexp_t\fP * start)"
Breadth first search for s-expressions\&. Depth first search will find the first occurrence of a string in an s-expression by basically finding the earliest occurrence in the string representation of the expression itself\&. Breadth first search will find the first occurrence of a string in relation to the structure of the expression itself (IE: the instance with the lowest depth will be found)\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIname\fP Value to search for\&. 
.br
\fIstart\fP Root element of the s-expression to search from\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
If the value is found, return a pointer to the first occurrence in a breadth-first traversal\&. NULL if not found\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SS "\fBsexp_t\fP * copy_sexp (const \fBsexp_t\fP * sx)"
Copy an s-expression\&. This is a deep copy - so the resulting s-expression shares no pointers with the original\&. The new one can be changed without damaging the contents of the original\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIsx\fP S-expression to copy\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
A pointer to a copy of sx\&. This is a deep copy, so no memory is shared between the original and the returned copy\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SS "\fBsexp_t\fP * find_sexp (const char * name, \fBsexp_t\fP * start)"
Find an atom in a sexpression data structure and return a pointer to it\&. Return NULL if the string doesn't occur anywhere as an atom\&. This is a depth-first search algorithm\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIname\fP Value to search for\&. 
.br
\fIstart\fP Root element of the s-expression to search from\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
If the value is found, return a pointer to the first occurrence in a depth-first traversal\&. NULL if not found\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SS "int sexp_list_length (const \fBsexp_t\fP * sx)"
Given an s-expression, determine the length of the list that it encodes\&. A null expression has length 0\&. An atom has length 1\&. A list has length equal to the number of \fBsexp_t\fP elements from the list head to the end of the ->next linked list from that point\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIsx\fP S-expression input\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
Number of \fBsexp_t\fP elements at the same level as sx, 0 for NULL, 1 for an atom\&. 
.RE
.PP

